THE FISCAL 2008 RESULTS INCLUDE AN ACCOUNTING GAIN RELATED TO THE ACQUISITION OF THE DISNEY STORES NORTH AMERICA AND A GAIN ON THE SALE OF MOVIES.COM

(TOGETHER $0.01 PER DILUTED SHARE), THE FAVORABLE RESOLUTION OF CERTAIN INCOME TAX MATTERS ($0.03 PER DILUTED SHARE), A BAD DEBT CHARGE FOR A RECEIVABLE FROM LEHMAN BROTHERS ($0.03 PER DILUTED SHARE) AND AN IMPAIRMENT CHARGE ($0.01 PER DILUTED

