COSTS AND EXPENSES

OPERATING EXPENSES INCLUDED AN INCREASE IN OPERATING

LABOR OF $173 MILLION FROM $3,105 MILLION TO $3,278 MILLION DRIVEN BY LABOR COST INFLATION AND HIGHER PENSION AND POSTRETIREMENT MEDICAL EXPENSES, PARTIALLY OFFSET BY A DECREASE IN COSTS OF SALES OF $57 MILLION FROM $1,167 MILLION TO $1,110 MILLION

DUE TO DECREASED SALES VOLUME. IN ADDITION, OPERATING EXPENSE REFLECTED INCREASED COSTS FOR NEW GUEST OFFERINGS

INCLUDING

WORLD OF COLOR

AT DISNEYLAND RESORT.

