THE DECREASE IN HOME ENTERTAINMENT REVENUES WAS PRIMARILY DUE TO A 25% DECREASE REFLECTING

LOWER UNIT SALES AND A 5% DECREASE DRIVEN BY LOWER NET EFFECTIVE PRICING REFLECTING THE OVERALL DECLINE IN THE DVD MARKET AND THE STRENGTH OF

PIRATES OF THE CARIBBEAN: AT WORLDS END

