NBC UNIVERSAL (NBCU) HELD 25%. THE COMPANY ACCOUNTED FOR THE TRANSACTION AS A SALE OF A PORTION OF ITS INTEREST IN LIFETIME WHICH RESULTED IN A $228 MILLION NON-CASH PRE-TAX GAIN ($142 MILLION

AFTER-TAX) REFLECTING THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN THE COMPANYS CARRYING AMOUNT OF THE LIFETIME INTEREST SOLD AND THE FAIR VALUE OF THE INCREMENTAL AETN INTEREST RECEIVED. FOLLOWING THE TRANSACTION THE COMPANYS OWNERSHIP INTEREST IN THE

