THE YEAR END 2010 AND 2009 BALANCES INCLUDE $473 MILLION AND $367 MILLION, RESPECTIVELY, THAT IF RECOGNIZED,

WOULD REDUCE OUR INCOME TAX EXPENSE AND EFFECTIVE TAX RATE. THESE AMOUNTS ARE NET OF THE OFFSETTING BENEFITS FROM OTHER TAX JURISDICTIONS.

